The paper discusses consistency criteria for replicated objects in distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Operating Systems (cs.OS), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Given that the paper focuses on consistency criteria for concurrent objects, it is most likely to belong to cs.DC and cs.DS. However, it also discusses implementation techniques and programming language considerations, which makes cs.PL and cs.SE likely categories as well. Finally, the paper's focus on distributed systems and fault-tolerance makes cs.OS a possible category.
